for (i in 1:7) {
  lprice_col <- paste("LPRICE", i, sep = "")
  lwhprice_col <- paste("LWHPRIC", i, sep = "")
  diff_col <- paste("diff", i, sep = "")
  
  # Create the difference column
  tuna[[diff_col]] <- tuna[[lprice_col]] - tuna[[lwhprice_col]]
}
diff_columns = paste0("diff", 1:7)

    theme_minimal()
  
  plots_list[[i]] = plot
}

Price elasticity

n_brands <- 7
# Define the column names for sales and prices
sales_cols <- paste0("MOVE", 1:n_brands)
price_cols <- paste0("LPRICE", 1:n_brands)

models <- list()

for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  # Build a formula: log(NSALEi) ~ LPRICE1 + LPRICE2 + ... + LPRICE7
  formula_str <- paste0("log(", sales_cols[i], ") ~ ", paste(price_cols, collapse = " + "))
  
  # Fit the model using lm()
  models[[i]] <- lm(as.formula(formula_str), data = tuna)
  
  cat("\n------ Model for Brand", i, "------\n")
  print(summary(models[[i]]))
}

Market Share (MCI)

n_brands <- 7

# market share
sales_cols <- paste0("MOVE", 1:n_brands)
for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  tuna[[paste0("share", i)]] <- tuna[[sales_cols[i]]] / tuna$FULLCUST
}
# Log-transform the market shares and then log-center them.
for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  tuna[[paste0("log_share", i)]] <- log(tuna[[paste0("share", i)]])
}
# Compute the average log share across all brands for each observation
tuna$avg_log_share <- rowMeans(tuna[, paste0("log_share", 1:n_brands)])
# Create centered log share variables for each brand:
for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  tuna[[paste0("centered_log_share", i)]] <- tuna[[paste0("log_share", i)]] - tuna$avg_log_share
}
# Step 3. Set up and run the MCI regression for each brand.
price_cols <- paste0("LPRICE", 1:n_brands)
tuna$avg_log_price <- rowMeans(tuna[, price_cols])


# log center price
for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  tuna[[paste0("centered_log_price", i)]] <- tuna[[paste0("LPRICE", i)]] - tuna$avg_log_price
}
# Run separate regressions for each brand
models <- list()
for(i in 1:n_brands) {
  formula_str <- paste0("centered_log_share", i, "~", "centered_log_price", i)
  models[[i]] <- lm(as.formula(formula_str), data = tuna)
  
  cat("\n------ Summary for Brand", i, "------\n")
  print(summary(models[[i]]))
}
